#  Sales Performance Dashboard (2024–2025)

<p align="center">
  <img src=" https://github.com/Estee200/EXCEL-PROJECTS/blob/main/E-Commerce%20Sales%20Performance%20Insight/E-commerce%20Insight.png" width="600">
</p>

##  Project Overview

This project presents an interactive **Sales Performance Dashboard** built in Microsoft Excel to analyze sales, profitability, regional performance, and product trends across two financial years (2024–2025).

The dashboard transforms transactional sales data into actionable business insights, enabling decision-makers to monitor KPIs, compare yearly performance, identify top-performing products, and evaluate regional sales distribution.

---

##  Business Problem

Sales information was stored as raw transactional records, making it difficult to monitor business performance, compare year-over-year growth, identify profitable products, and evaluate regional sales trends.

Management required a centralized dashboard that could provide a clear view of sales performance and support better business decisions.

---

##  Dataset

The dataset contains sales transactions captured between **2024 and 2025**, including:

- Date
- Product
- Category
- Region
- Sales
- Quantity Sold
- Cost

From these fields, additional business metrics such as **Profit** and Year-over-Year comparisons were derived for reporting.

---

##  Data Preparation

The raw dataset was transformed using **Power Query**, where data quality checks and standardization were performed before loading into Excel.

Preparation included:

- Cleaning inconsistent values
- Formatting dates
- Creating calculated columns
- Structuring the data for Pivot Tables
- Building reusable reporting tables

---

##  Dashboard Features

The dashboard provides decision-makers with an interactive overview of business performance through:

### Executive KPIs

- Total Sales
- Total Quantity Sold
- Total Cost
- Total Profit
- Year-over-Year KPI comparison

### Revenue Trend Analysis

Visualizes monthly sales performance for **2024 vs 2025**, making seasonal trends and revenue growth easy to identify.

### Regional Sales Distribution

Compares sales performance across different business regions to identify high-performing markets.

### Product Performance

Ranks products based on generated sales, helping management identify best-selling and underperforming products.

### Interactive Filtering

Users can dynamically filter the report by:

- Product Category
- Reporting Year

---

##  Key Business Insights

- Sales increased significantly in 2025 compared to 2024, indicating positive business growth.
- Monitor and Mouse generated the highest sales revenue across the reporting period.
- Southern and Eastern regions contributed the largest share of total sales.
- Monthly trends reveal clear seasonal fluctuations that can support future inventory and marketing planning.
- Interactive filtering allows managers to evaluate performance by product category and reporting year.

---

##  Business Value

This dashboard enables management to:

- Monitor overall business performance
- Compare yearly sales growth
- Identify high-performing products
- Evaluate regional performance
- Support pricing and inventory planning
- Improve data-driven decision-making

